news.title: Indore civic body seals three shops for commercial use of basements
news.para: Acting on the directives issued by collector Asheesh Singh, a joint team comprising officials from the district administration and Indore Municipal Corporation sealed the basements of four buildings that were found to be exploiting parking spaces for commercial activities.

news.title: Gaurs Group to launch its IPO in next 18 months: Manoj Gaur, CMD
news.para: ​​ Byoued by the successful launch of its luxury housing project in Ghaziabad clocking Rs 3,100 crore sales in three days, Gaur said the company has set a target to expand its business of development of housing projects across the Delhi-NCR market.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Indirapuram residents protest against pollution from dumping yard
news.para: The dumpyard, spread over 10 acres, is on a vacant land behind the Khoda police station. Residents alleged that over 100 trucks dispose of their waste at this site daily, resulting in tonnes of garbage accumulating in the yard.

news.title: Hyderabad: Dharani panel suggests third-party audit of portal
news.para: It also said the maintenance of the Dharani portal should be given to govt agencies such as National Informatics Centre (NIC), Centre for Good Governance (CGG), or TSOnline, as the govt data should be protected and address privacy concerns. As of now, the Dharani portal is being managed by a private agency.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body initiates QR code facility for depositing house tax
news.para: With the new system, residents will not only have the convenience of depositing house tax from their residences, but will also get an additional 2.5% rebate in house tax.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP seals illegal flats in Palam Vihar after HC notice
news.para: The building, located at House No 913, had been previously sealed due to unauthorised construction, but the owner unlawfully broke the seal and resumed activities.

news.title: Nexus Venture Partners sells stake in India Shelter Finance for Rs 482 crore
news.para: US-based Nexus Venture Partners, through its affiliates Nexus Ventures III and Nexus Opportunity Fund II Ltd, offloaded 64 lakh shares, amounting to a 5.97 per cent stake in India Shelter Finance Corporation through two separate bulk deals on the BSE.

news.title: Bombay HC slams SRA for delayed Kanjur village slum survey
news.para: Justices Mahesh Sonak and Kamal Khata on Sept 11 directed SRA to file a detailed affidavit explaining the reasons why no survey has been conducted despite HC's Nov 18, 2022, order to finish it within six months.

news.title: Delhi development body extends final payment deadline for Dwarka flats
news.para: The new deadline for making the 25% payment of the total value is now Sept 30, Earlier, it was Aug 31. The authority said the decision was in response to buyers' requests as they needed more time to arrange for money. The deadline was pushed back also because finishing work is going on in the flats.

news.title: MahaRERA grants relief to over 70 Ruparel Skygreens buyers over delayed possession
news.para: The promoter had failed to deliver possession to the allottees — including those who had booked the flats under the subvention schem, and the construction link plan scheme — by the dates agreed and the MahaRERA completion date of Dec 2021.

news.title: Noida authority to launch 1,200 plots for multiple schemes
news.para: During a recent meeting chaired by CEO Lokesh M, the civil department provided a report according to which 1,190 vacant plots across sectors in work circles 1 to 10 are vacant.

news.title: Table Space acquires five lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru for Rs 500 crore
news.para: The company has acquired 5 lakh square feet of office space in Whitefield, Bengaluru, for about Rs 500 crore, sources said.

news.title: Noida: NMRC offers three commercial plots near Okhla Bird Sanctuary station
news.para: Currently, NMRC operates Aqua Line, which stretches 29.7 km from Sector 51 to Depot Station in Greater Noida. Since its launch in Jan 2019, the line has experienced a notable increase in daily ridership, growing from 18,000 passengers in 2019 to 55,000 in 2024.

news.title: Delhi HC restrains transfer of shares of Oberoi Hotel companies following inheritance dispute
news.para: The court passed the interim order on a lawsuit by the late businessman's daughter Anastasia Oberoi and her mother Mirjana Jojic Oberoi against Anastasia's brother Vikramjit Singh Oberoi, sister Natasha Devi Oberoi, cousin Arjun Singh Oberoi and others.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to take legal advice on property, land issues: Punjab governor
news.para: The administrator said a follow-up meeting with the chairpersons of the council’s sub-committees and other key dignitaries to resolve long-standing issues and guide policy decisions will be held.

news.title: Delhi’s rural residents protest at Jantar Mantar over unresolved issues
news.para: The mahapanchayat saw participation from residents of all 360 villages in Delhi, as well as several villages from neighbouring Haryana. They presented ten demands, including tax exemptions, amendments to the land pooling policy, and the development of Delhi's villages into smart villages.

news.title: Hyderabad: Illegal building permissions rise after 51 villages merge with municipalities
news.para: Leading the charge, it is alleged, were none other than officials of the merged gram panchayats who were brazenly issuing the building permissions. Even on the day the state govt issued merger notification, thousands of such permissions were given in the 51 villages.

news.title: PM inaugurates phase II of metro connecting Ahmedabad and Gandhinagar
news.para: Gujarat Governor Acharya Devvrat and Chief Minister Bhupendra Patel accompanied the prime minister on his metro journey, during which he interacted with students and other passengers.

news.title: Huda prepares revised master plan for development of Hubballi-Dharwad
news.para: The Huda is now seriously considering implementing the revised draft of the master plan to ensure that all taxpayers of the twin cities get proper roads, drinking water connections, proper UGD, and other basic amenities.

news.title: Arkade Developers' IPO subscribed 5.79 times on September 16
news.para: The portion meant for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 8.03 times while the quota for non-institutional investors received 7.89 times subscription. The category for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) attracted 24 per cent subscription.
